                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d540">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Italy/201</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Italian Chargé (<persName type="from">Diana</persName>) to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Chargé d’Affaires of Italy presents his compliments to His Excellency the
                    Secretary of State and has the honor, by order of his Government, to inform the
                    Department of State that, in conformity with the deliberation of December 5,
                    1932, by the Grand Council of Fascism, the Italian Ministry of Finance has
                    remitted to-day to the United States Treasury the sum of $1,245.437 (one
                    million, two hundred forty five thousand, four hundred thirty seven dollars)
                    being the amount of the quota of the Italian war debt towards the United States,
                    due December 15, 1932.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-15">December 15,
                            1932</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
